Tracking employee progress is essential for maximizing the impact of training programs. By using an LMS, employers can monitor participation, completion rates, quiz scores, and skill assessments. Whether implementing best online learning platforms or pursuing professional advancement through programs like Master of Education Online, accurate measurement allows organizations to enhance training strategies and improve performance outcomes.

---

### Tracking Course Completion

One of the simplest ways to measure employee progress is by monitoring course completion rates. Online learning platforms integrated with LMS provide automated tracking of modules completed by each employee. At Strawket, our LMS solutions generate detailed reports showing which employees have finished courses and which may need additional support. This helps managers ensure that training goals are being met efficiently.

---

### Assessing Knowledge Retention

Beyond course completion, knowledge retention is a key indicator of progress. LMS platforms offer quizzes, tests, and interactive assessments to evaluate how well employees understand the material. Employees engaged in [online doctoral programs](https://strawket.com/) or professional courses can demonstrate their learning through these assessments. Strawket helps organizations use these insights to identify gaps and reinforce learning where needed.

